You need to import the WorkerParameters class in order to use its Builder class.

Import statement:

```
import androidx.work.WorkerParameters;
```

Then, replace the code with the following:

```
SortWorker sortWorker = new SortWorker(requireActivity(), new WorkerParameters.Builder().build(), productAdapter);
sortWorker.sortProducts();

// устанавливаем адаптер для отображения списка товаров
RecyclerView recyclerView = v.findViewById(R.id.recycler_view_products);
recyclerView.setAdapter(productAdapter);
recyclerView.setLayoutManager(new LinearLayoutManager(requireActivity()));
```

Note that we updated the first line to use `requireActivity()` instead of `getActivity()` since `getActivity()` returns null in some cases.

You may need to update your dependencies to include the latest version of the WorkManager library. The Builder class was added in version 2.3.0 of the WorkManager library, so if you are using an older version, you may not have access to it.

Try updating the WorkManager library by adding the following to your app module's build.gradle file:

```
dependencies {
    // ...
    implementation 'androidx.work:work-runtime:2.5.0'
}
```

Note that the version number may change depending on what is the latest version available.

Then, sync your project and try building again. This should fix the error and allow you to use the Builder class to create WorkerParameters objects.

